PC diffuser film is a specialized optical component based on polycarbonate (PC). Through a proprietary co‑extrusion process, a uniform functional coating and a non‑uniform anti‑stick coating are formed on opposite surfaces of the film. When light traverses these layers, diffuse reflection and scattering convert a point light source into a uniform surface light source, delivering effective light diffusion for a wide range of display and lighting applications.

